column74: I find that we are assigned readings about people of different backgrounds, but not by people of different backgrounds, if that makes sense.

I just wish that all kids had equal punishments and equal treatment. Ive been at sierra Canyon since kindergarten. Im in 8th grade now and nothing has changed regarding how each kid is treated. If i got caught cheating on a test i would be suspended or expelled but if someone who was richer than me got caught cheating they would get a warning. Another example is dress code. There are so many kids my age and older wearing basically whatever they want and never get dress coded but when i wore one white t-shit that showed midrift only when i raised my arms, one day and i got dress coded in the first class i attended. Things like this i know can't really change because private school are run like businesses but it would be nice to see a little change.

Sierra Canyon is a really great school. My main criticism is that the Performing Arts program is chaotic - After "Spring Awakening" was performed, major architectural changes occurred and certain teachers made it especially difficult for newcomers to join the program, which was very disappointing for me as I always liked theater and wanted to perform in plays. At Sierra Canyon I have participated in several plays, although in every play directed by that teacher I was given parts with no lines. I have only been in two plays with lines, one of which had only 3 lines and one of which I was a main character and did very well in. I think if Sierra Canyon put half the effort it puts into the Athletics program towards the Performing Arts program, then many students would be much happier.
